  May 7,  2014</strong>  BBC    Five perplexing questions about computers in 2039</strong>   By Aviva Rutkin</strong>     
Why do plants need their own Facebook, again? To understand this question, you need to know about Plantastic, the brainchild of Bill Tomlinson at the University of California, Irvine and colleagues.... Plantastic...would advise what plants would work best for your area and tell you what people in the neighborhood are growing. Nanochips on plants would feed data back to the site. That information in turn could be used to learn more about what grows best in which environment.


  
 Read the full story on the 
 BBC  website. 

   
   
   
   
   

